  "coverStory": {
    "title": {
      "zh": "夸克的自旋默契：RHIC實驗揭開強核力中的量子關聯奧秘",
      "en": "The Spin Connection: Quantum Correlations Revealed in QCD Confinement"
    },
    "summary": {
      "zh": "【結果】短距離ΛΛ̄對的自旋關聯度達0.181±0.035(stat)±0.022(sys)，統計顯著性達4.4個標準差。當配對距離增加，相關性急劇下降，證實量子退相干現象。實驗數據與SU(6)夸克模型預測高度吻合，表明初始夸克對的自旋平行狀態在強子化中基本保持。這不僅驗證了手徵對稱性破缺的真空凝聚態，更為未來量子計算模擬QCD提供關鍵驗證點。",
      "en": "**Results:** Short-range ΛΛ̄ pairs showed significant positive spin correlation (P=0.181±0.035±0.022), with 4.4σ significance. Correlation vanishes at larger separations, revealing quantum decoherence during hadronization. Data align with SU(6) model predictions for spin-aligned quark pairs. This validates the chiral condensate's role in confinement and provides critical benchmarks for quantum computing simulations of nonperturbative QCD."
    },
